# Figma Section Implementation Rule

> Pre-flight: confirm you have read `CLAUDE.md` and `PROGRESS.md` before step 1.

---

## AUTO-LOOP MODE

If the user provides multiple frame node IDs in one message, the agent runs
the full 11-step process for section 1, verifies it with the browser agent,
confirms it passes, updates PROGRESS.md, then immediately moves to section 2
— no pause, no waiting for user input between sections.

Only stop the loop if:
- A section has unresolvable missing assets after all attempts (log `[!]`, continue)
- A discrepancy cannot be fixed after 3 attempts (log `[!]`, continue)
- The user explicitly says "stop after this section"

After ALL sections are done, send one final summary:
- Full page screenshot at CANVAS_W px (desktop)
- Full page screenshot at 375px (mobile)
- List of any `[!]` issues needing attention
- Tokens added
- Missing assets logged

---

## Step 0 — Context Load

Read in this exact order before touching any tool or file:
1. `CLAUDE.md` — all project rules, what is done, token reference
2. `PROGRESS.md` — current section count N, what frame maps to what file
3. `src/tokens/design-tokens.ts` — full token list (never duplicate)
4. Skim `src/components/sections/home/Concept.tsx` — canonical reference implementation.
   Do NOT use Hero.tsx as a reference — it has a known desktop/mobile text duplication violation.

---

## Step 1 — Fetch the Frame

Call `get_figma_data` with the provided `fileKey` and `nodeId`. Record:

| Field | MCP path | Use |
|-------|----------|-----|
| Frame name | `name` | Confirms what section this is |
| Width | `dimensions.width` | → `CANVAS_W` |
| Height | `dimensions.height` | → `CANVAS_H` |
| Page Y position | `locationRelativeToParent.y` on parent artboard | → page order |
| Background | `fills[0]` | → section background |

If hierarchy is unclear, list all sibling frame IDs sorted by `locationRelativeToParent.y`
to confirm the correct insertion order.

---

## Step 2 — Determine File Name and Section Number

1. Check `PROGRESS.md` for the next available section number N.
2. Check `src/components/sections/[page-name]/` for existing files.
3. Before creating anything — check if a visually identical section already exists in:
   - `src/components/sections/home/`
   - `src/components/sections/marketplace/`
   If yes → import it directly, do not rebuild.
4. Name the file `PascalCase.tsx` from the section's **visible heading or badge text**.
   - Badge "THE CONCEPT" + heading "App Store" → `Concept.tsx`
   - Heading "Built for reliability and trust" → `TrustReliability.tsx`
5. Never name a file after a Figma frame ID.

---

## Step 3 — Read Every Property (recursively)

For every child node at every level, record:

| Property | MCP field |
|----------|-----------|
| x, y position | `locationRelativeToParent.x`, `.y` |
| Width, height | `dimensions.width`, `.height` |
| Fill | `fills` — solid hex, linear gradient (angle + stops), radial gradient |
| Border | `strokes`, `strokeWeight`, `borderRadius` (each corner if mixed) |
| Shadow / blur | `effects` — type, x, y, blur, spread, color, opacity |
| Typography | `textStyle.fontFamily`, `.fontWeight`, `.fontSize`, `.lineHeight`, `.letterSpacing`, `.textAlign` |
| Text content | `text` — preserve `\n` line breaks exactly |

**Resolve every `globalVars.styles` reference** (`layout_XXX`, `fill_XXX`, `style_XXX`,
`effect_XXX`) before writing any code. If a property is unclear, call `get_figma_data`
again on that specific node ID — never guess.

---

## Step 4 — Write the Layout Map Comment

Before writing any JSX, write this comment at the top of the new file.
It must be complete enough for another agent to recreate the section from it alone.

```typescript
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// [ComponentName].tsx  —  "[Visible section heading]"
// Figma frame: [FRAME_ID]  "[Figma frame name]"
// Canvas: [CANVAS_W] × [CANVAS_H] px   Page-y: [Y]   bg: [color]
//
// Responsive strategy:
//   ≥ 768 px  →  Scaled cqw canvas  (100cqw / [CANVAS_W]px)
//   < 768 px  →  Stacked reflow, fluid clamp() font sizes
//
// LAYOUT MAP  (all coords are section-absolute Figma px):
//   [Node name]   (x=[X], y=[Y])   [W]×[H]   [style summary]
//   [Node name]   (x=[X], y=[Y])   [W]×[H]   [style summary]
//   ...
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

---

## Step 5 — Export Assets

For every image, icon, or SVG node:

1. **Check `public/` first** — if the asset already exists, use it directly.
2. If not: call `download_figma_images` with the node ID.
3. Save to the correct folder:
   - Home page sections → `public/section-[N]/[descriptive-kebab-name].svg` or `.png`
   - All other pages → `public/section-[N]-[page-name]/[descriptive-kebab-name].svg` or `.png`
     (N restarts from 1 for each new page — never use global sequential numbers across pages)
   - Complex SVGs with `NaN` path segments → export as `.png` instead.
   - If MCP output path differs from project path, copy the file manually.
4. **Export fails completely** → inline the SVG data from MCP `fills` / children.
5. **Never use a placeholder.** Never skip an asset.
6. Truly unresolvable → log under `MISSING ASSETS:` in `PROGRESS.md` and stop.

---

## Step 6 — Token Check

1. Open `src/tokens/design-tokens.ts`.
2. For every value from Step 3:
   - Matching token exists → use `colors.xxx`, `typography.fonts.xxx`, `radiuses.xxx`.
   - Value appears ≥ 2 times in this section, no token exists → append to bottom of its group in the token file.
   - Value appears only once → declare as `const` at the top of the component file only.
3. Never rename, reorder, or delete existing tokens.

Available token groups:
- `colors.white/black`, `colors.brand`, `colors.gradient`, `colors.text`,
  `colors.background`, `colors.status`, `colors.overlay`, `colors.border`
- `typography.fonts` (inter, poppins, jakarta, mono)
- `radiuses` (card="24px", cardLg="32px", cardSm="12px", pill="16px",
  full="9999px", icon="12px", inputIcon="8px", tag="4px")

Import `radiuses` in every section file — never hardcode `borderRadius` values.

---

## Step 7 — Implement the Section

### Skeleton (use exactly this structure)

```typescript
import Image from "next/image";
import { colors, typography, radiuses } from "@/tokens/design-tokens";

// [Layout Map from Step 4]

const CANVAS_W = /* exact Figma frame width — e.g. 1280 */;
const CANVAS_H = /* exact Figma frame height */;
const SCALE = `calc(100cqw / ${CANVAS_W}px)`;

// One-off values not in tokens (used < 2 times in this section):
// const BADGE_COLOR = "#ba9eff";

export default function SectionName() {
  return (
    <>
      <SectionDesktop />
      <SectionMobile />
    </>
  );
}

// ─── Desktop ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

function SectionDesktop() {
  return (
    <section
      className="relative hidden w-full overflow-hidden md:block"
      style={{
        backgroundColor: colors.background.section,
        aspectRatio: `${CANVAS_W} / ${CANVAS_H}`,
        containerType: "inline-size",
      }}
    >
      <div
        className="absolute left-0 top-0"
        style={{
          width: CANVAS_W,
          height: CANVAS_H,
          transform: `scale(${SCALE})`,
          transformOrigin: "top left",
        }}
      >
        {/* Every child: position absolute, exact Figma left/top/width/height */}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}

// ─── Mobile ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

function SectionMobile() {
  return (
    <section
      className="relative block w-full overflow-hidden md:hidden"
      style={{ backgroundColor: colors.background.section }}
    >
      <div className="flex flex-col gap-8 px-6 py-16">
        {/* Same sub-components as desktop, different fontSize / lineHeight props */}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

---

### Desktop Canvas Rules (non-negotiable)

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| `hidden md:block` | Hides desktop canvas on mobile |
| `aspectRatio: CANVAS_W / CANVAS_H` | Reserves proportional height — no fixed heights ever |
| `containerType: "inline-size"` | Enables `cqw` units for scale |
| `overflow-hidden` | Clips decorative bleeds |
| Inner div: `absolute left-0 top-0` | NOT `mx-auto` — breaks left edge alignment |
| Inner div: fixed px `width` + `height` | Exact Figma canvas dimensions |
| Scale: `calc(100cqw / ${CANVAS_W}px)` | Use `cqw` — `vw` double-counts scrollbar width |
| `transformOrigin: "top left"` | Scales from the correct anchor |
| Every child: `position: absolute` | With inline `style={{ left: X, top: Y, width: W, height: H }}` |
| Typography: always inline `style` | `fontFamily`, `fontWeight`, `fontSize`, `lineHeight`, `letterSpacing` — never Tailwind text utilities |

---

### Typography Templates

**Standard text node:**
```typescript
<p
  className="absolute m-0"
  style={{
    left: X, top: Y, width: W,
    fontFamily: typography.fonts.poppins,
    fontWeight: 500,
    fontSize: FS,
    lineHeight: `${LH}px`,
    letterSpacing: `${LS}em`,
    color: colors.text.heading,
  }}
>
  {text}
</p>
```

**Gradient text:**
```typescript
<h2
  className="absolute m-0"
  style={{
    left: X, top: Y, width: W,
    fontFamily: typography.fonts.poppins,
    fontWeight: 700,
    fontSize: FS,
    lineHeight: `${LH}px`,
    background: `linear-gradient(${ANGLE}deg, ${STOP_1}, ${STOP_2})`,
    WebkitBackgroundClip: "text",
    WebkitTextFillColor: "transparent",
    backgroundClip: "text",
  }}
>
  {text}
</h2>
```

---

### Gradients and Shadows

- Reproduce every gradient stop, angle, and opacity exactly from Figma `GRADIENT_LINEAR` / `GRADIENT_RADIAL`.
- Reproduce every shadow from `effects` in exact order: `x y blur spread color`.
  - If Figma shadow matches Tailwind `shadow-xl` exactly → use `className="shadow-xl"`.
  - Otherwise → `style={{ boxShadow: "Xpx Ypx BLURpx SPREADpx rgba(...)" }}`.
- Multiple shadows → comma-separate in the string; order matters.

---

### Shared Sub-Components Pattern

When desktop and mobile render the same element with different sizing — extract it:

```typescript
function SectionHeading({
  fontSize,
  lineHeight,
}: {
  fontSize: number | string;
  lineHeight: string;
}) {
  return (
    <h2
      style={{
        margin: 0,
        fontFamily: typography.fonts.poppins,
        fontWeight: 600,
        fontSize,
        lineHeight,
        color: colors.text.heading,
      }}
    >
      Heading copy — lives in ONE place only
    </h2>
  );
}

// Desktop: <SectionHeading fontSize={48} lineHeight="60px" />
// Mobile:  <SectionHeading fontSize="clamp(28px, 8vw, 40px)" lineHeight="1.2" />
```

Text content must **never** be duplicated between desktop and mobile.

---

### Mobile Layout Rules

- `block md:hidden` on the section wrapper.
- Tailwind flex/grid with `px-6 py-16` as the base padding.
- Fluid font sizes: `fontSize: "clamp(28px, 8vw, 40px)"` — never fixed px on mobile headings.
- Preserve brand: colours, gradients, key hero images. Simplify layout, not identity.
- Horizontal logo / partner strips → `overflow-x-auto` with flex row so all logos are reachable.

