## Step 8 — Wire into `page.tsx`

1. Read `src/app/[page-name]/page.tsx`.
2. Add the import in positional order matching Figma y-order.
3. Insert `<SectionName />` at the correct vertical position.
4. Keep numbered comments consistent — shift only if needed by the insertion.
5. **Do not move or modify any other section.**

---

## Step 9 — Verification Loop (non-skippable)

1. Start dev server if not running: `npm run dev`
2. Open Cursor browser agent, navigate to `http://localhost:3000/[page-path]`
3. Set viewport to exactly **CANVAS_W px wide** (no fixed height — height is driven
   by `aspectRatio`, section fills edge-to-edge)
   — at CANVAS_W, `scale()` = 1 giving a true 1:1 pixel comparison against Figma
4. Scroll to the section being verified and take a screenshot
5. Fetch the Figma frame image via Figma MCP
6. Compare systematically and list every discrepancy with exact px values:

   | Check | Detail |
   |-------|--------|
   | Position | Every element x, y |
   | Size | Width, height of every element |
   | Typography | fontFamily, fontSize, fontWeight, lineHeight, color |
   | Colors | Backgrounds, fills, borders |
   | Gradients | Angle, stops, opacity |
   | Shadows | x, y, blur, spread, color |
   | Images/icons | Correct asset, correct size |
   | Edge-to-edge | Section fills full browser width — no gaps or white margins |

   Example discrepancy list:
   > 1. Heading top: 96px rendered vs 82px Figma — fix
   > 2. Right edge has 2px white gap — section width not 100%
   > 3. Badge border opacity 0.1 rendered vs 0.2 Figma — fix

7. Fix all discrepancies in code
8. Re-screenshot at CANVAS_W to confirm fixes
9. Resize browser to a **different desktop width** (e.g. 1440px if CANVAS_W is 1280px)
   — verify section still fills edge-to-edge and scales proportionally, no overflow
10. Set viewport to **375px wide** — verify `block md:hidden` layout is readable,
    stacked, full width, brand colours and gradients preserved
11. Mark done only when all three viewport checks pass

