## Pre-Done Checklist

Run before declaring any section complete:

- [ ] `aspectRatio` matches Figma frame's exact `CANVAS_W / CANVAS_H`
- [ ] Scale uses `100cqw`, not `100vw`
- [ ] `containerType: "inline-size"` on the outer section
- [ ] Inner canvas div is `absolute left-0 top-0` — not `mx-auto`
- [ ] Every desktop child has inline `left`, `top`, `width`, `height` from Figma
- [ ] All typography uses inline `style` — no Tailwind text-size utilities
- [ ] All gradients reproduce exact angle, stops, opacity from Figma
- [ ] All shadows reproduce exact values from Figma `effects`, correct order
- [ ] All assets in correct `public/section-[N]-[page-name]/` folder, no placeholders
- [ ] Design tokens reused; new ones appended at bottom of their group only
- [ ] `radiuses` imported and used — no hardcoded `borderRadius` values
- [ ] Mobile wrapper present with fluid font sizes and brand preserved
- [ ] Text content lives in shared sub-components — never duplicated desktop/mobile
- [ ] `page.tsx` updated with import + JSX in correct position
- [ ] No other section file was modified
- [ ] Browser agent screenshot at CANVAS_W px matches Figma ✓
- [ ] Browser agent screenshot at 375px — mobile readable and brand preserved ✓
- [ ] `PROGRESS.md` marked `[x]` with full section detail block

---

## Absolute Forbidden Actions

- Skipping browser agent verification screenshots.
- Marking `[x]` without both desktop (CANVAS_W) and mobile (375px) browser agent screenshots passing.
- Using Tailwind `text-*` utilities for Figma font sizes or line heights.
- Using `vw` in the scale formula — always `cqw`.
- Using `mx-auto` on the inner canvas div.
- Capping scale with `min(1, …)`.
- Placing mobile JSX before desktop JSX in the file.
- Hardcoding a color, radius, or font that exists as a token.
- Hardcoding a `borderRadius` value — always use `radiuses` tokens.
- Duplicating text content between desktop and mobile — shared sub-components always.
- Using Hero.tsx as a reference implementation — it has a text duplication violation.
- Moving or reordering any section in an existing `page.tsx`.
- Touching `Header.tsx`, `Footer.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, any home section, or any marketplace section.
- Creating `SECTION_MANIFEST.json`, `PAGE_THEME.json`, or any undeclared JSON file.
- Importing `fs from 'fs'` or any Node.js module in `page.tsx`.
- Creating `public/images/` subfolders.
- Reusing section numbers across pages — each page restarts from 1.
- Modifying any file not in: new section file, its assets folder,
  `page.tsx`, `design-tokens.ts`, `PROGRESS.md`.
